hic origin of these lineages is still uncertain and will not be answered until more fossils are found. It is most probable that Mystacina dispersed from Australia to New Zealand while other noctilionoid bats either remained in or dispersed to South America.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Teeling, Emma C", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Madsen, Ole", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Murphy, William J", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Springer, Mark S", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "O'Brien, Stephen J", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/42d71b1fa3b2303276c65a1513b0e226", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/fd6db8b04ba60a8db12330b761b5e922bc20d5967387d9040100262574ff29f9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/R9PV8H3X", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/R9PV8H3X", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/5acb0450773591418e127bf48189e688!/b29494-31960", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "2", "pages": "308-319", "title": "Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution", "volume": "28"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/42d71b1fa3b2303276c65a1513b0e226"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:R9PV8H3X"}